title: Identify a condensed, rounded, san-serif typeface
content:
Does this typeface look familiar to anyone?  
\_

 ![](http://web.archive.org/web/20150317150744im_/http:/typophile.com/files/forums-wordmark_4759.jpg)
  

 ![](http://web.archive.org/web/20150317150744im_/http:/typophile.com/files/forums-wordmark_4408.jpg)

Font: 

 Asap + Dosis 

Solved By: 

 [kthomps5](http://web.archive.org/web/20150317150744/http:/typophile.com/user/175823 "View user profile.")
author: RusselQ

comments.content:
|FORUMS| appears to be Asap, a free Google web font:  
 [http://www.google.com/fonts/specimen/Asap](http://web.archive.org/web/20150317150744/http:/www.google.com/fonts/specimen/Asap "http://www.google.com/fonts/specimen/Asap")

|CORPORATE EVENT PLANNING| appears to be another Google font, Dosis:  
 [http://www.google.com/fonts/specimen/Dosis](http://web.archive.org/web/20150317150744/http:/www.google.com/fonts/specimen/Dosis "http://www.google.com/fonts/specimen/Dosis")
Yup, you nailed it. Didn't even consider that they might be 2 different typefaces. Thanks for the help!
